        "text": "Malachi 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It does not occur elsewhere. The oven among the Hebrews was in the form of a large \"pot,\" and was heated from within by placing the wood inside of it. Of course, while being heated, it had the appearance of a furnace. The meaning here is that the wicked would be consumed or destroyed \"as if\" they were such a burning oven; as if they were set on fire, and burned up.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord shall swallow them up in his wrath - The same idea of the utter destruction of the wicked is here presented under another form - that they would be destroyed as if the earth should open and swallow them up. Perhaps the allusion in the language is to the case of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram, Numbers 16:32; compare Psalm 106:17.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The Lord shall swallow them up in his wrath - The same idea of the utter destruction of the wicked is here presented under another form - that they would be destroyed as if the earth should open and swallow them up. Perhaps the allusion in the language is to the case of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram, ",
            "children": []
