  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt make them as a fiery oven",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] R.V., as a fiery furnace.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The comparison is condensed, and inexact in form; but the sense is clear: thou wilt consume them as fuel in a furnace. The phrase is figurative (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Malachi 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): yet there may be an allusion to the terrible vengeance inflicted on the Ammonites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 12:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in the time of thine anger",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Lit. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in the time of thy countenance",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "presence:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " when Thou appearest in person. Cp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 17:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ‘The face of Jehovah’ is the manifestation of His Presence in wrath as well as in mercy (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 34:16",
